definition: on top/upon/above/upper/previous/first (of multiple parts)/to climb/to get onto/to go up/to attend (class or university)

sentences.english: Only God radiates at level seven.
sentences.chinese: 只有上帝才能達到第七級。

sentences.english: Enlightenment, it seems, always comes from an earnest study of the Word of God.
sentences.chinese: 啓迪似乎總是從懇切地研究上帝的道而來。

sentences.english: Even the GOD cannot guarantee everyone would be better.
sentences.chinese: 上帝也不能保祐每一個人。

sentences.english: This god was not identified with nature.
sentences.chinese: 上帝已經不再等同於自然了。

sentences.english: Moses manages to placate God momentarily, and then he turns around to face the people.
sentences.chinese: 摩西想馬上安撫上帝，他把臉轉向人民。

sentences.english: What if last night God destroyed my soul and put in a new soul?
sentences.chinese: 如果昨晚上帝毀掉了我的靈魂並創造了新的那怎麼辦？

sentences.english: God, that was a beautiful sight.
sentences.chinese: 上帝，那是一幅多美的景色。

sentences.english: The LORD finds us enough reasons for prayer, and we ought to thank Him that it is so.
sentences.chinese: 上帝樂意聽我們的瑣碎絮語，我們也該爲此獻上感謝。

sentences.english: And through prayer, God helps me put into practice what I learn.
sentences.chinese: 藉着禱告，上帝幫助我把所明白的東西付諸實踐。

sentences.english: Please, Lord, give me no more than 10years.
sentences.chinese: 請上帝最多讓我活10年吧。

sentences.english: There is the reader. There is God.
I burnt some joss papers and pray to the examination god.
sentences.chinese: 我燒了一些金紙，祈求上帝的考試。

sentences.english: B    God is the all powerful creator and sustainer of the Universe.
sentences.chinese: 上帝是宇宙間萬能的創造者和支撐者。

sentences.english: God  making contact withs to forgive you.
In the same way, the Lord took the time and effort to stitch you together.
sentences.chinese: 同樣的，上帝也是一針一線把你縫紉起來。

sentences.english: Am I trying to do the job that cupid or God suppose to do?
sentences.chinese: 我是否嘗試著做上帝跟邱比特的工作？

definition: God (in Catholicism)/abbr. for 天主教[Tian1 zhu3 jiao4], Catholicism
(third person pronoun for a divine being)
Jehovah (biblical name for God, Hebrew: YHWH)/compare Yahweh 雅威[Ya3 wei1] and God 上帝[Shang4 di4]
Holy Father/God the Father (in the Christian Trinity)
